text:
News #LastNightInSweden: celebrities and the Swedish mock Donald Trump's bizarre claims Donald Trump made a vague reference to an occurrence in Sweden and people from Chelsea Clinton to the Swedish Embassy are trying to work out what he meant Credit: REUTERS/Kevin Lamarque Helena Horton 20 February 2017 • 8:49am 
D onald Trump has baffled everyone from politicians to celebrities with the strange claims he made about Sweden over the weekend. 
Although he has insisted his reference was to an as yet unidentified Fox News story, many have been left trying to figure out exactly what he meant. 
"You look at what's happening last night in Sweden," Mr Trump said. "Sweden. Who would believe this? Sweden. They took in large numbers. They're having problems like they never thought possible." 
No incident occurred in Sweden and the country's baffled government asked the US State Department to explain. 
Of course, jokes and memes sprung up on social media and people sprang up to share their views about what on Earth happened in Sweden. Chelsea Clinton made a joke What happened in Sweden Friday night?
